# 
# To configure environment variables in GitHub Codespaces:
# 1. Go to GitHub Repository Settings
# 2. Navigate to Secrets and Variables > Codespaces
# 3. Add repository secrets for sensitive data (passwords, keys)
# 4. Add repository variables for non-sensitive configuration
# 
# Required Secrets for Codespaces:
# - AZURE_SQL_PASSWORD
# 
# Required Variables for Codespaces:
# - AZURE_SQL_SERVER
# - AZURE_SQL_DATABASE  
# - AZURE_SQL_USER
# - AZURE_SQL_PORT
# - RCI_MAX_INTERVAL_SEC
# - RCI_MAX_DISTANCE_M
# - RCI_MIN_SPEED_KMH

# =============================================================================
# APPLICATION CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Data filtering thresholds
RCI_MAX_INTERVAL_SEC=15      # Maximum time between data points (seconds)
RCI_MAX_DISTANCE_M=100       # Maximum distance between data points (meters)  
RCI_MIN_SPEED_KMH=7          # Minimum speed for data recording (km/h)

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================
# Environment Detection:
# - Local: No WEBSITE_SITE_NAME or CODESPACES environment variables
# - Azure Web App: WEBSITE_SITE_NAME environment variable present
# - GitHub Codespaces: CODESPACES environment variable present
#
# The application automatically detects the environment and loads configuration
# from the appropriate source (this .env file for local, environment variables
# for deployed/cloud environments)